{
    "title": "Italian Confetti Pasta Salad",
    "ingredients": [
        "2 cups tri-colored rotini pasta",
        "1 cup mayonnaise",
        "1 tablespoon red wine vinegar",
        "1 clove garlic, minced",
        "1 teaspoon salt",
        "¼ teaspoon ground black pepper",
        "1 ½ tablespoons chopped fresh basil",
        "1 cup chopped tomatoes",
        "½ cup chopped yellow bell pepper",
        "½ cup sliced black olives"
    ],
    "core_ingredients": [
        "tri-colored rotini pasta",
        "mayonnaise",
        "red wine vinegar",
        "garlic",
        "salt",
        "black pepper",
        "basil",
        "tomatoes",
        "yellow bell pepper",
        "black olives"
    ],
    "instructions": "1. Fill a large pot with lightly salted water and bring to a rolling boil. Stir in rotini and return to a boil. Cook pasta uncovered, stirring occasionally, until tender yet firm to the bite, about 8 minutes. Drain and rinse with cold water; set aside. 2. Whisk mayonnaise, vinegar, garlic, salt, and black pepper together in a large bowl until combined. Stir in basil. 3. Stir in rotini, tomatoes, bell pepper, and olives gently until combined. Chill in the refrigerator for 3 hours to overnight. Stir gently before serving.",
